<br>
Anyway, here's the quest : Catla, a somewhat ambitious woman (her dialogs are quite humorous, as she tries to hide her greed behind generous reasons) wants to tap into powerful magics, guarded by the wise Valkyn. She asks you to steal or acquire scrolls from Kylliki (sp ?). You have the choice to either ask her to give you the scrolls when she is at home (it is the guard tower near the newbie zone), or to steal them when she is away (she patrols back and forth between her house and the docks). I asked her and honestly told Catla sent me, she finally gave up and gave me the scrolls, warning me or Catla to not misuse them.<br>
Here you have the choice between using the scrolls yourself or giving them to Catla. Guessing the spell would backfire (I was right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), I played the &quot;honest&quot; guy and gave the scrolls to Catla, who asked me in turn to get 3 totems from 3 different kind of Morvalt, who dwell east of the stone bridge, around a lot of Morvalt camps. They were easy to find, and one shot kills. I saw one level 15 bonedancer soloing them, so I guess it is approx this level.<br>
You then have the possibility to use the totems yourself or give them to Catla. I decided to give them to Catla. She the proceeded to cast the spell ... which backfired and hurt her (like I guessed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). She thanked me anyway for her help, and gave me as a reward this item :<br>
<br>
Ukjent Musikk Leggings : studded legginfs AF 32 (lvl 16) qua100% bonus 10% strength3 charisma3 battlesongs2. A pretty nice low level item, for a quest which is easier imho than the berbenet leggings.<br>
<br>
Hope I will find equally nice high level quests on shrouded isle.<br>
Also, I took part in a raid on the Tuskaran Glacier (sp ?). We killed one giant named skeleton who dropped a fantastic one handed axe, legion quality. I don't remember the bonus exactly, but it had  15 cha and 4 (useless <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) in battlesong. The only axe skald was exstatic, the weapon looked great too like a big sword with two protruding axe baldes on either side. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roseannelottsa>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/13/02 1:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nice low level quest on Aegir</span><hr size=1> Wow, nice sounding quest!<br>
